docs.snippet: MONTREAL, Feb. 25 (Canadian Press). -- The possibility of Charlie Conacher of Toronto being over-taken by any other marksman before the National Hockey League season ends appeared remote tonight. Official scoring figures show him with 8 points mor...
docs.lead_paragraph: MONTREAL, Feb. 25 (Canadian Press). -- The possibility of Charlie Conacher of Toronto being over-taken by any other marksman before the National Hockey League season ends appeared remote tonight. Official scoring figures show him with 8 points more than Frank Boucher, New York Ranger centre, his nearest rival.

headline.main: BOUCHER REMAINS SECOND IN SCORING; Rangers' Star, With 37 Points, Has Little Chance of Over-taking Conacher.
